---
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Me"
  description="Principal Site Reliability Engineer at Atypon, a Wiley Brand"
  pubDate={new Date('March 25 2024')}
  heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
  <div class="profile-container">
    <img src="/blog/profile.jpg" alt="Hamdan Radaideh" class="profile-image" />
  </div>

  <p>
    Hello! I&apos;m Hamdan Radaideh, a Principal Site Reliability Engineer and Team Lead at Atypon,
    a Wiley Brand. I specialize in creating highly available, secure, and scalable solutions for
    systems and web platforms. With certifications including GIAC with honors, CKA, GHA, and Google
    Cloud Professional Cloud Architect (PCA), I apply DevSecOps and cybersecurity practices to drive
    standardization and modularization across complex environments.
  </p>

  <h2>Current Role</h2>
  <h3>Principal DevOps and Site Reliability Engineer / Team Lead (June 2024 - Present)</h3>
  <p>At Atypon, a John Wiley and Sons Brand, I lead a high-performance DevOps team:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Built and led high-performance DevOps team, driving modularization across projects</li>
    <li>
      Co-built HashiCorp Vault using Bank-Vaults FW and Vault Agent integration with mutation
      webhooks
    </li>
    <li>Supervised OpenTelemetry (Otel) adoption stack with Grafana Alloy Agents</li>
    <li>Supervised ArgoCD adoption for continuous delivery</li>
    <li>Managed GitHub Actions workflows with Arc over GKE</li>
    <li>Led implementation of WIF with OIDC in GCP for secure identity management</li>
    <li>
      Enabled dynamic identity for on-premises workloads by onboarding to SPIRE/SPIFFE framework
    </li>
    <li>
      Integrated Cloudflare Zero Trust using Terraform and Warp Agents for site-to-site connections
    </li>
    <li>
      Built SSO integration with Active Directory (AD), GCP, Google Secure LDAP, and custom local
      LDAP schema
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Previous Experience</h2>
  <h3>Senior DevOps Engineer (2021 - 2024)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Automated Proxmox hypervisor installation and clustering via PXE</li>
    <li>Managed Atlantis and Citizen for Terraform automation</li>
    <li>Deployed HA Zabbix with cronosync and DRBD</li>
    <li>Automated VM template creation with Packer, Preseed, and Ansible</li>
    <li>Adoption of Puppet Configuration management system</li>
    <li>Managed GCP networking and IAM with Terraform</li>
    <li>Managed Kubernetes clusters (DC and Cloud) with Rancher and GKE</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Mid-Level DevOps Engineer (2018 - 2021)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Dockerized applications and integrated with Kubernetes</li>
    <li>Developed BigIP integration for pool/iRule management</li>
    <li>Automated Jenkins-to-Jira reporting via REST API with Groovy pipelines</li>
    <li>Created Helm charts for Kubernetes deployments</li>
    <li>
      Managed ELK stack, Solr, Zookeeper, EFK, PostgreSQL, Prometheus and Grafana in Kubernetes
    </li>
    <li>Administered GCP, AWS with CloudFormation, Azure with Azure DevOps using Terraform IaC</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Technical Skills</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Container Orchestration: Kubernetes (CKA certified), Docker, Rancher</li>
    <li>Cloud Platforms: GCP (PCA certified), AWS, Azure</li>
    <li>
      Infrastructure as Code: Terraform (HashiCorp certified), Terragrunt, Ansible, Packer, Puppet
    </li>
    <li>CI/CD: GitHub Actions (GHA certified), ArgoCD, Jenkins</li>
    <li>Security: Vault, SPIRE/SPIFFE, Cloudflare Zero Trust, GIAC GSEC certified</li>
    <li>Observability: OpenTelemetry, Prometheus, Grafana, ELK/EFK, Zabbix</li>
    <li>Programming: Python, Golang, Bash, JavaScript, Ruby on Rails</li>
    <li>Networking: Proxmox, Netbox, iptables, tshark, TCP dump</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Certifications</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Google Cloud Professional Cloud Architect (PCA)</li>
    <li>GIAC Security Essentials Certification (GSEC) - with honors</li>
    <li>Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) - The Linux Foundation</li>
    <li>GitHub Actions (GHA) - GitHub</li>
    <li>HashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate</li>
    <li>GIAC Advisory Board Member</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Education</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      Master of Engineering - Computer Engineering, Embedded Systems (2020-2023)<br />
      Yarmouk University - With honors, first of class, 92.1%
    </li>
    <li>
      Bachelor&apos;s degree - Computer Engineering (2012-2016)<br />
      Yarmouk University
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Philosophy</h2>
  <p>
    I believe in the power of continuous learning and sharing knowledge. With a strong command of
    tools like Vault, Kubernetes, and Terraform, I lead teams in automating cloud infrastructure,
    CI/CD pipelines, and observability stacks to optimize for both scalability and security.
    I&apos;m passionate about:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Building highly available and secure distributed systems</li>
    <li>Implementing DevSecOps and cybersecurity best practices</li>
    <li>Driving standardization and modularization across complex environments</li>
    <li>Leading high-performing teams in infrastructure automation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Connect With Me</h2>
  <p>
    You can find me on <a href="https://github.com/halradaideh" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
      >GitHub</a
    >, <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/hamdan-a-radaideh/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"
      >LinkedIn</a
    >, and <a
      href="https://www.credly.com/users/hamdan-al-radaideh"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noreferrer">Credly</a
    >. I&apos;m always interested in discussing technology, sharing experiences, and collaborating
    on interesting projects.
  </p>
</Layout>

